Exclude equations that can't be evaluated.

Source: R/default_equations.R
fixme_exclude_failing_equations.Rd

This function tries to evaluate allodb equations and excludes the ones that err.

fixme_exclude_failing_equations(data)

Arguments

data

An equations dataframe, e.g. allodb::master().

Value

A dataframe with all equations that can be successfully evaluated.

See also

Other internal functions that flag issues to be fixed: fixme_pull_failing_eqn, fixme_units, handle_multiple_rowid

Examples

fixme_exclude_failing_equations(allodb::master())
